There was a worker coming to fix the kitchen floor, and I pretended to be working from home, but in reality I was editing "Addicted."
If only this damned file would open. (OneDrive is such a piece of crap.)
*Hacker's voice* I'm in.
He started drilling, and the noise was super loud. Great.
Turn the air purifier to the maximum setting, which felt a bit too aggressive, but I really did smell the wood shavings, so it was justified, especially since he also opposed wearing masks. And I did need to protect myself, didn't I?
I really want to go back to sleep, but I can't until he leaves.
Good news: Chapter Four is finally edited!
Chapter Five is very long and makes me super anxious. Yay! It's so exciting.
Searching and replacing... ➡️ ellipsis, there are 54 of them in this chapter 😅
But I still insist on this. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally charged.
The floor repair worker is using a vacuum cleaner, hoping that this means he is about to finish.
He went out (it sounded like) cutting something. I secretly checked the progress. There is still a lot of work to do :(
Chapter Five still has 7 pages left. This is still my favorite chapter, and the draft is in quite good shape, mainly just some formatting adjustments and minor tweaks for active voice and conciseness. But I really need a break, a cup of tea, while that guy is still working in my kitchen.
He started using the vacuum cleaner again. Hoping this is a good sign.
The kitchen floor repair worker has left!
He told me that he quoted the price for the entire floor repair, but the landlord is too cheap and only willing to pay for the damaged section near the entrance. It feels much better.
I am drinking tea in the garden, while the air purifier in the kitchen is working hard to clean the air in the room!
